                            <h2 style="margin: 20px 0 15px 0; color: #2F4F4F; font-size: 18px; border-left: 4px solid #2F4F4F; padding-left: 10px;">Issue Resolution</h2>
                            
                            <div style="background-color: #f8f9fa; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                                <h3 style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; color: #CD853F; font-size: 16px;">Google Business Location Optimization</h3>
                                
                                <p style="color: #333333; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                                    <strong>Issue:</strong> Because Longmont Dog Training doesn't have a physical address, Google currently lists Erie as the primary service area, affecting local search visibility.
                                </p>
                                
                                <p style="color: #333333; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                                    <strong>Solution:</strong> We're reordering service areas to list Longmont first, adding more Longmont-specific content, and building up local reviews to improve ranking in local searches.
                                </p>
                                
                                <p style="color: #333333; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5;">
                                    <strong>Expected Impact:</strong> This adjustment should improve visibility in Longmont searches within 4-6 weeks as we build local content and reviews.
                                </p>
